{"word":"ἄγονος","slug":"ἄγονος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄγονος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γίγνομαι'><el>γίγνομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>unborn</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <i>not yet born</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>not producing, unfruitful, barren</i>; <el>τόκοισιν ἀγόνοις</el> travail <i>without issue, bringing no children to the birth</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>not productive of, barren in</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>childless</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}